com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.ouch.translator

Class UnsignedSmartFIXMessageFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.configuration.registry.Registerable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.SmartFIXMessageFactory
        • com.camerontec.catalys.server.adapter.ouch.translator.UnsignedSmartFIXMessageFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFIXMessageFactory, ISmartFIXMessageFactory, IRegisterable

    public class UnsignedSmartFIXMessageFactory
extends SmartFIXMessageFactory
    FIX message factory that is intended to perform unsigned arithmetic on long values.

    This factory is used for Borsa Instabul OUCH translation where numeric fields are unsigned.

    Only overrides methods we need. All other methods will end up calling the methods in SmartFIXMessageFactory

    Author:
    Jairam Gottapu

      • createFIXFill

        public IFIXMessage createFIXFill(ITagValues order,
                                 Decimal quantity,
                                 Decimal price,
                                 String execID)
        Description copied from interface: ISmartFIXMessageFactory
        Basic fill execution report is created using values taken from order and the trade quantity and price given.

        Note that the order is not updated (eg CumQty, AvgPx, LeavesQty).

        Specified by:
        createFIXFill in interface ISmartFIXMessageFactory
        Overrides:
        createFIXFill in class SmartFIXMessageFactory
        Parameters:
        order - Order on which fill is based.
        quantity - Quantity of this trade (LastShares).
        price - Price of this trade (LastPx).
        execID - Execution report execid - should be unique.
        Returns:
        Fill execution report.
